# Test Data JSON Conventions

## File Location

`data/test_N/{skill}/partM.json` where N=1-20, skill=reading|listening|writing|speaking, M=part number.

## Reading JSON Structure

```json
{
  "part": 1,
  "title": "Part Title",
  "type": "correspondence|diagram|information|viewpoints",
  "instructions": "Instructions text",
  "sections": [
    {
      "section_type": "passage|questions|diagram_email|response_passage",
      "content": "Text with __DROPDOWN_X__ placeholders",
      "questions": [
        { "id": 1, "text": "Question text", "options": ["A", "B", "C", "D"], "answer": 0 }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

- `answer` is a 0-based index into the `options` array
- `__DROPDOWN_X__` placeholders (X = question id) are replaced with HTML selects at render time
- Part 3 has 5 options (A-E), where E = "Not Given"

## Listening JSON — Parts 1-3 (per_question_audio)

```json
{
  "part": 1, "type": "listening", "layout": "per_question_audio",
  "listening_type": "audio", "mediaType": "audio",
  "sub_parts": [{ "id": "1.1", "passageAudioUrl": "", "questions": [...] }],
  "sections": [{ "section_type": "questions", "questions": [...] }]
}
```

- `sub_parts` organizes questions by conversation section (UI uses this)
- `sections` is a flat list of ALL questions (answer key uses this)
- Each question has `audioUrl` for per-question audio
- Questions may have optional `imageUrl` for image-based answers

## Listening JSON — Parts 4-6 (full_questions)

```json
{
  "part": 4, "type": "listening", "layout": "full_questions",
  "listening_type": "audio|video", "mediaType": "audio|video",
  "mediaUrl": "cloudinary-url", "sections": [...]
}
```

- Part 5 uses `"listening_type": "video"` and `"mediaType": "video"`
- Question `text` is a sentence stem completed by the selected option

## Audio/Video URLs

- Cloudinary pattern: `https://res.cloudinary.com/YOUR_CLOUD_NAME/video/upload/v.../filename.m4a`
- Use empty strings `""` as placeholders when media isn't available yet
- File naming: `pY-pas.m4a` (passage), `pY-qN.m4a` (question), `p1-S-pas.m4a` (Part 1 section)

## Validation

```bash
python -m json.tool data/test_X/skill/partY.json
```
